{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|1Ch|8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","chapter":8,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":1,"text":"Benjamin fathered Bela, his firstborn; Ashbel was born second, Aharah third,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":2,"text":"Nohah fourth, and Rapha fifth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":3,"text":"Bela’s sons: Addar, Gera, Abihud,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":4,"text":"Abishua, Naaman, Ahoah,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":5,"text":"Gera, Shephuphan, and Huram.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":6,"text":"These were Ehud’s sons, who were the heads of the families living in Geba and who were deported to Manahath:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":7,"text":"Naaman, Ahijah, and Gera. Gera deported them and was the father of Uzza and Ahihud.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":8,"text":"Shaharaim had sons in the territory of Moab after he had divorced his wives Hushim and Baara.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":9,"text":"His sons by his wife Hodesh: Jobab, Zibia, Mesha, Malcam,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":10,"text":"Jeuz, Sachia, and Mirmah. These were his sons, family heads.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":11,"text":"He also had sons by Hushim: Abitub and Elpaal.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":12,"text":"Elpaal’s sons: Eber, Misham, and Shemed who built Ono and Lod and its surrounding villages,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":13,"text":"Beriah and Shema, who were the family heads of Aijalon’s residents and who drove out the residents of Gath,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":14,"text":"Ahio, Shashak, and Jeremoth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":15,"text":"Zebadiah, Arad, Eder,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":16,"text":"Michael, Ishpah, and Joha were Beriah’s sons.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":17,"text":"Zebadiah, Meshullam, Hizki, Heber,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":18,"text":"Ishmerai, Izliah, and Jobab were Elpaal’s sons.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":19,"text":"Jakim, Zichri, Zabdi,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":20,"text":"Elienai, Zillethai, Eliel,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":21,"text":"Adaiah, Beraiah, and Shimrath were Shimei’s sons.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":22,"text":"Ishpan, Eber, Eliel,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":23,"text":"Abdon, Zichri, Hanan,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":24,"text":"Hananiah, Elam, Anthothijah,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":25,"text":"Iphdeiah, and Penuel were Shashak’s sons.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":26,"text":"Shamsherai, Shehariah, Athaliah,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":27,"text":"Jaareshiah, Elijah, and Zichri were Jeroham’s sons.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":28,"text":"These were family heads, chiefs according to their family records; they lived in Jerusalem.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":29,"text":"Jeiel fathered Gibeon and lived in Gibeon. His wife’s name was Maacah.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":30,"text":"Abdon was his firstborn son, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Nadab,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":31,"text":"Gedor, Ahio, Zecher,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":32,"text":"and Mikloth who fathered Shimeah. These also lived opposite their relatives in Jerusalem, with their other relatives.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:33","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":33,"text":"Ner fathered Kish, Kish fathered Saul, and Saul fathered Jonathan, Malchishua, Abinadab, and Esh-baal.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:34","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":34,"text":"Jonathan’s son was Merib-baal, and Merib-baal fathered Micah.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:35","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":35,"text":"Micah’s sons: Pithon, Melech, Tarea, and Ahaz.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:36","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":36,"text":"Ahaz fathered Jehoaddah, Jehoaddah fathered Alemeth, Azmaveth, and Zimri, and Zimri fathered Moza.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:37","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":37,"text":"Moza fathered Binea. His son was Raphah, his son Elasah, and his son Azel.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:38","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":38,"text":"Azel had six sons, and these were their names: Azrikam, Bocheru, Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan. All these were Azel’s sons.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:39","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":39,"text":"His brother Eshek’s sons: Ulam was his firstborn, Jeush second, and Eliphelet third.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:40","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","bookOrder":12,"chapter":8,"verse":40,"text":"Ulam’s sons were valiant warriors and archers. They had many sons and grandsons —150 of them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"1Ch","chapter":8,"paragraphStarts":[1,3,6,8,12,15,17,19,22,26,28,29,33,34,35,36,37,38,39,40],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Benjamin’s Descendants"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:8:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Benjamin "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 46:21","book":"Gen","chapter":46,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 26:38","book":"Num",